# React components and style utilities

## File and export names

- Place UI components under `components/atoms`, `components/molecules`, or `components/organisms`, each in its **own folder** with **`index.ts`** (see `component-module-layout.mdc`).
- **File name = default export component name**, both **PascalCase** (e.g. `atoms/Button/Button.tsx` exports `Button`, `molecules/Header/Header.tsx` exports `Header`).
- Exception: under **`components/ui/<primitive>/`**, the main file may be **lowercase** (e.g. `button/button.tsx`) to match shadcn conventions; **`*-variants.ts`** stays kebab-case.
- always use **arrow function** components and non-components

## Style helpers (no abbreviations)

- Use **`classNames`** from `@/libs/utils/classNames/classNames` for clsx + tailwind-merge. Do **not** use **`cn`**.
- Use **`tailwindVariants`** as the binding for tailwind-variants: `import { tv as tailwindVariants } from "tailwind-variants"`. Do **not** call **`tv`** directly in source.

## Server vs client

- Keep **`tailwindVariants`** style definitions in **server-safe** modules (no `"use client"`) when they must be used from Server Components (e.g. `components/ui/button/button-variants.ts`). Interactive wrappers stay in `"use client"` files.

## Linting

- **Oxlint** does not enforce PascalCase filenames; follow this rule when adding components.
